summary: This document is a set of notes from a June 12, 2023 call between an SDNY prosecutor and attorney Jeanne Christensen regarding a potential sex trafficking case involving a minor victim. The notes discuss coordination between the SDNY and the DANY (District Attorney New York) offices, jurisdictional issues, and victim safety protocols.

persons.name: Jeanne Christensen
persons.context: She is the counsel for a minor victim in a potential sex trafficking case and participated in a call with the SDNY to discuss the case and victim safety concerns.

events.title: Call Regarding Minor Victim Trafficking Case
events.description: A call took place between an SDNY prosecutor and attorney Jeanne Christensen to discuss a potential sex trafficking investigation involving a minor victim, jurisdictional issues between SDNY and DANY, and victim safety protocols.

keyFacts: A minor victim of sex trafficking was interviewed by the District Attorney New York (DANY).
The SDNY and DANY are coordinating ('deconflicting') to determine which office will handle the case, with SDNY indicating they have not yet opened an investigation.
The alleged sex trafficking of the minor occurred approximately twice in New York, with the remainder occurring in Florida and the US Virgin Islands.
Attorney Jeanne Christensen expressed safety concerns for the minor victim regarding the subject(s) of a potential investigation.
The SDNY outlined its protocol for discussing victim safety and the timing of contacting investigation subjects with victim's counsel before proceeding.
